                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.75/10: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spam</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moore</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Sebastian</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-03T15:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 3, 1924—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>41. Your 38, August 29, 7 p.m. As noted in royal decree, copy of which was
                    forwarded several months ago to the Department,<note n="16" xml:id="d607fn16"
                        >Not printed.</note> the concession was open to proposals from all
                    countries. There was only one American company<note n="17" xml:id="d607fn17">The
                        International Telephone and Telegraph Co.</note> which sought the
                    concession. The issue narrowed down to which telephone system should be adopted,
                    the American or the Swedish. I naturally thought that American system would be
                    favored by the Department. My assistance consisted in informing Spaniards that
                    American business interests always knew how to carry out big projects and that
                    the American telephone system was not equaled anywhere. In the future I shall
                    make no recommendations before receiving instructions from the Department. I am
                    forwarding by mail copies of the decree.<note n="16" xml:id="d607fn18">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
